<BaseLayout title="Python Overview · CS Notebook">
  <article class="space-y-6">
    <header>
      <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-primary-cyan mb-2">Languages / Python</p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">
        <Bilingual><span slot="zh">Python 概览</span><span slot="en">Python Overview</span></Bilingual>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">
        <Bilingual>
          <span slot="zh">Python 以<b>开发效率</b>换取<b>运行效率</b>——动态类型、自动内存管理、海量第三方库让它成为游戏工具链、AI/数据、服务端脚本的事实标准。它的核心设计"一切皆对象 + 解释执行"带来了灵活性，也带来了 GIL 与性能代价。本页从执行模型、GIL、与 C++ 的取舍三个维度建立对 Python 的整体认知。点击下方切换 GIL 在 CPU 密集与 I/O 密集场景下的行为差异。</span>
          <span slot="en">Python trades <b>runtime efficiency</b> for <b>developer efficiency</b> — dynamic typing, automatic memory management, and a massive ecosystem make it the de facto standard for game tooling, AI/data, and server scripting. Its core design of "everything is an object + interpreted execution" brings flexibility but also the GIL and performance costs. This page builds a holistic understanding from three angles: execution model, GIL, and the trade-off vs C++. Toggle below to see how the GIL behaves under CPU-bound vs I/O-bound workloads.</span>
        </Bilingual>
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- 交互：GIL 时间轴 -->
    <div class="glass p-5" data-viz="gil-timeline">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-4">
        <button class="btn gil-btn btn-primary" data-mode="cpu">
          <span data-lang="zh">CPU 密集</span><span data-lang="en">CPU-bound</span>
        </button>
        <button class="btn gil-btn" data-mode="io">
